"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670155","HM Treasury","false","2017-01-23","<p>HM Treasury published its analysis on the long-term economic impact of EU membership and the alternatives in April 2016, and it was approved by ministers.</p><p> </p><p>The Government continues to undertake a range of analysis to inform the UK’s position for the upcoming EU exit negotiations. We are seeking the best possible arrangements for the United Kingdom and the work being conducted reflects this.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2017-01-23T16:08:09.523Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670155/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670155/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-01-09","Overseas Trade","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the report by the Cambridge Centre for Business Research in its report <i>The Macro-Economic Impact of Brexit</i>, as revised in January 2017, which concluded that the pre-referendum analysis by HM Treasury of the potential impact of Brexit on various outcomes for trade outside the EU was flawed, who drafted the forecasts, and what ministerial scrutiny was given to those forecasts prior to publication.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL4475"
