"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670165","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-17","<p>A wide range of safety and contingency measures are in place to ensure the safe movement of Defence Nuclear Materials throughout the UK. These are regulated and assessed by the Defence Nuclear Safety Regulator. Ministry of Defence officials have regular discussions with all relevant agencies including local authorities and emergency services, the Police and National Traffic Information Services, including those in Scotland.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-17T16:08:31.127Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670165/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670165/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-09","Nuclear Weapons: Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with the (a) Scottish Government and (b) local authorities in Scotland on the safety framework for nuclear convoys travelling through Scotland.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","59203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670166","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-12","<p>I refer my right hon. Friend to the answer given by my hon. Friend the former Minister for Defence Procurement (Mr Philip Dunne) on 4 December 2015 to Question 17860 to the hon. Member for Garston and Halewood (Maria Eagle).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-12T16:05:39.977Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670166/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670166/answer","20151204_17860_HMS_Ocean.docx","20151204_17860_HMS_Ocean.docx","17860 - WQnA extract on HMS Ocean","17860 - WQnA extract on HMS Ocean","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670166/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-09","HMS Ocean: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons HMS Ocean is being decommissioned in 2018.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","59209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670167","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-16","<p>The next edition of Joint Doctrine Publication 0-30 <em>UK Air and Space Doctrine</em> will refer to the employment of unmanned and remotely piloted aircraft systems but will not discuss specific systems. Greater detail will be contained in Joint Doctrine Publication 0-30.2 <em>The UK Approach to Unmanned Aircraft Systems</em>.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-16T16:09:24.403Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670167/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670167/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670167/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-09","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Joint Doctrine Publication 0-30, entitled UK Air Space Doctrine, will cover the use of unmanned aerial vehicles.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","59206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670168","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-16","<p>Following extensive consultation across Defence and the academic community, and having drawn on similar work from sources such as NATO and the United States Air Force, the next edition of Joint Doctrine Publication 0-30 <em>Air and Space Doctrine</em> remains on track for publication in 2017.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-16T16:08:43.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670168/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670168/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/670168/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-09","Air Space","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress has been made on finalising the Joint Doctrine Publication 0-30, entitled UK Air Space Doctrine.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","59207"
